com.palomamobile.android.sdk.media

Interface IMediaService


  • public interface IMediaService
    This interface is consumed by the Retrofit library to provide access to the Paloma Mobile Platform Media Service RESTful API. All calls are synchronous. To get a concrete implementation of this interface call IServiceManager.getService() This class provides somewhat low level access to the Server API it may be more convenient to use methods in IMediaManager.
    See Also:
    Paloma Mobile Platform Media Service RESTful API

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Response postMediaPrivate(String requestId, long userId, TypedInput file)
      Upload file content, the posted content is accessible only to the authenticated user that originally posted the content.
      Response postMediaPublic(String requestId, TypedInput file)
      Upload file content, the posted content is accessible to anyone who can access the media url.

      • postMediaPublic

        Response postMediaPublic(String requestId,
                       TypedInput file)
        Upload file content, the posted content is accessible to anyone who can access the media url.
        Parameters:
        requestId - for the purposes of identifying retries
        file - file to upload
        Returns:
        raw Response rather than MediaInfo because the media url is returned in a header. JobUploadMediaPublic provides a convenient wrapper, consider using it instead.
